    FRFLABEL FRF Label Information Table624 Main Index Contains a list of all user-defined FRF excitation DOFs along with their labels For excitation DOFs defined via FRFXIT entries, labels are defined by the user For excitation DOFs defined via FRFXIT1 entries, blanks are assumed for the labels Record 3 - HEADER Record 4 - DATA Record 5 - TRAILER FRFLABEL FRF Label Information Table Word Name Type Description 1 NAME(2) CHAR4 Data block name Word Name Type Description 1 XITCOD I Coded excitation DOF - See Note below 2 LABEL(12) CHAR4 Label for the excitation DOF Words 1 through 13 repeat until End of Record Word Name Type Description 1 WORD1 I T otal number of user-defined excitation DOFs 2 WORD2 I Number of excitation DOFs defined via FRFXIT entries 3 WORD3 I 0 4 WORD4 I 0 5 WORD5 I 0 6 WORD6 I 0 Notes: 1.For excitation DOFs defined via FRFXIT entries, XITCOD = 10*(Point ID) + Excitation DOF 2.For excitation DOFs defined via FRFXIT1 entries, XITCOD = 10*(Point ID) + 7

    625 FRL Frequency Response List Main Index The FRL contains one logical record for each different frequency set defined in the bulk data. Each record contains a sorted list of the unique frequencies defined in the set. Record 1 - HEADER Record 2 - Repeat Record 3 - TRAILER FRL Frequency Response List Word Name Type Description 1 NAME(2) CHAR4 Data block name 3 SETID I Set ID1 thru Set IDn Word 3 repeats until End of Record Word Name Type Description 1 FREQ RS Radian frequencies belonging to set IDi (w = 2pf) Word Name Type Description 1 WORD1 I number of frequency sets 2 WORD2 I = 0 3 WORD3 I = 0 4 WORD4 I = 0 5 WORD5 I = 0 6 WORD6 I = 0 Notes: 1.In the rare case when # frequencies < # processors, WORD3 will contain the minimum number of frequencies in any subcase/FREQ* entry selected. Used only in direct frequency response. Otherwise, WORD3 will be 0.
